{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01S3qoCfuirJ1rG9oVN5pquC","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Backend — Developer Guide\n2\t\n3\t## Structure\n4\t\n5\t```text\n6\tsrc/                    — Hono API server, routes, workers, middleware, waitlist entrypoint\n7\tmigrations/             — SQL migrations auto-run on startup\n8\tpackages/anchor-client/ — IDL bridge (generated from solana/target/)\n9\tpackages/game-engine/   — Game logic, PDA derivation, verification\n10\tpackages/fairness/      — Fairness verification functions\n11\tpackages/config/        — Shared configuration\n12\t```\n13\t\n14\t## Commands\n15\t\n16\t```bash\n17\tpnpm dev          # Start dev server (backend service)\n18\tpnpm dev:waitlist # Start waitlist-only entrypoint\n19\tpnpm test         # Run all tests (vitest)\n20\tpnpm lint         # Lint backend + workspace packages\n21\tpnpm lint:fix     # Lint + autofix backend + workspace packages\n22\tpnpm typecheck    # Typecheck backend + workspace packages\n23\tpnpm migrate      # Run DB migrations\n24\tpnpm format       # Format with prettier\n25\t```\n26\t\n27\t## App Platform Env Contract\n28\t\n29\t- If you add, remove, rename, or make any runtime/deploy env var mandatory, update the repo-owned App Platform contract in the same task.\n30\t- Update both `.do/app-dev.yaml` and `.do/app-prod.yaml`.\n31\t- If deploy-time inputs changed, also update `.github/workflows/deploy-dev.yml`, `.github/workflows/deploy-prod.yml`, and `.do/README.md`.\n32\t- Do not assume missing GitHub Environment vars/secrets are safe; empty values can reach App Platform as empty strings and must be handled deliberately.\n33\t\n34\t## Pre-commit Hook\n35\t\n36\t`.githooks/pre-commit` typechecks affected backend files or workspace packages when they are staged.\n37\t\n38\tGit must be configured to use it: `git config core.hooksPath .githooks`\n39\t\n40\t## Database\n41\t\n42\t- **Engine**: PostgreSQL 16 (via `postgres` package, typed raw SQL)\n43\t- **Migrations**: `migrations/001_init.sql` — single consolidated file, auto-run on startup\n44\t- **Key tables**:\n45\t  - `rounds` — flipyou + pot shot matches (commit-reveal, CHECK on game/phase)\n46\t  - `closecall_rounds` — Close Call pari-mutuel rounds (oracle-resolved, CHECK on phase/outcome)\n47\t  - `game_entries` — **single source of truth** for participation + stats + leaderboard. Written at create/bet time, UPSERT'd at settlement. Has `user_id`, `side`, `is_winner`, `settled_at`.\n48\t  - `transactions` — real on-chain SOL movements (deposit/payout/refund with tx_sig)\n49\t  - `player_profiles` — player identity (user_id, username, avatar)\n50\t  - `closecall_candles` — cached minute-boundary BTC prices (BRIN indexed)\n51\t  - `auth_challenges` / `refresh_tokens` — JWT auth\n52\t  - `referral_codes` / `referral_links` / `referral_earnings` / `referral_claims` — referral system\n53\t  - `event_queue` — async event processing\n54\t  - `operator_events` — operator audit log\n55\t- **Schema conventions**: `BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY` (not BIGSERIAL), CHECK constraints on enum TEXT columns, `TIMESTAMPTZ` for all timestamps\n56\t\n57\t## Routes\n58\t\n59\t| Path prefix | Purpose |\n60\t|-------------|---------|\n61\t| `/auth/*` | Challenge-response JWT auth |\n62\t| `/flipyou/*` | FlipYou create, settle, verify |\n63\t| `/pot-shot/*` | Pot Shot create, current round |\n64\t| `/rounds/*` | Shared round lookup, verification |\n65\t| `/closecall/*` | Close Call betting, rounds, history |\n66\t| `/profile/*` | Player profile, stats, transactions |\n67\t| `/referral/*` | Referral codes, links, earnings, claims |\n68\t| `/price/*` | SOL/USD price endpoint |\n69\t\n70\t## Public API Contract\n71\t\n72\t- Treat the public backend API as contract-first.\n73\t- For any public route change, update in the same task:\n74\t  - shared request/response contract\n75\t  - runtime route parsing or serialization\n76\t  - OpenAPI path or schema\n77\t  - endpoint tests\n78\t- Prefer shared validator-backed contracts over handwritten OpenAPI schemas.\n79\t- Do not duplicate public game IDs, error shapes, or reusable envelopes.\n80\t- Every new public route file should have a matching OpenAPI path module.\n81\t- Keep `admin` and `internal` routes out of the public OpenAPI spec unless explicitly requested.\n82\t- Public JSON routes must use the shared envelope body:\n83\t  - success: `{ ok: true, data }`\n84\t  - error: `{ ok: false, error }`\n85\t- Preserve semantic HTTP status codes. Do not flatten handled failures into `200`.\n86\t  - `200` / `201` / `202`: success\n87\t  - `204`: explicit no-body success\n88\t  - `400` / `422`: malformed or invalid request\n89\t  - `401` / `403`: auth or permission failure\n90\t  - `404`: missing resource\n91\t  - `409`: conflict or invalid current state\n92\t  - `429`: rate limit or cooldown\n93\t- Only use `200` with nullable, empty, or default-valued payloads when the absence is the documented success answer for that route.\n94\t- When changing a public route contract, audit status-sensitive consumers in `waitlist/`, `webapp/`, and `telegram/`, or log the rollout gap in `docs/TECH_DEBT.md`.\n95\t- Canonical reference for this pattern: `docs/specs/304-response-envelope/spec.md`.\n96\t\n97\t## Settlement\n98\t\n99\t- **PDA watcher** (`worker/pda-watcher.ts`): WebSocket `onAccountChange` for instant join/settle detection\n100\t- **Polling fallback** (`worker/settlement.ts`): 1s interval for resilience\n101\t- **Close Call clock** (`worker/closecall-clock.ts`): Creates rounds on minute boundaries, settles via Pyth price\n102\t- **Retry worker** (`worker/retry.ts`): Retries failed settlements with exponential backoff\n103\t\n104\t## Package Conventions\n105\t\n106\t- Package names: `@rng-utopia/*` (private, no npm publish)\n107\t- All amounts in **lamports** (u64) — convert SOL only at display boundaries\n108\t- Fees read from on-chain `PlatformConfig.fee_bps` at settlement time\n109\t- Auth: JWT Bearer tokens via challenge-response (not per-request Ed25519 signatures)\n110\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"736bbedb-6401-4318-a325-ee85001d8ebf","uuid":"4b83a751-97d8-4947-8d5f-20a2b1e7beea","timestamp":"2026-04-22T11:20:23.432Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/CLAUDE.md","content":"# Backend — Developer Guide\n\n## Structure\n\n```text\nsrc/                    — Hono API server, routes, workers, middleware, waitlist entrypoint\nmigrations/             — SQL migrations auto-run on startup\npackages/anchor-client/ — IDL bridge (generated from solana/target/)\npackages/game-engine/   — Game logic, PDA derivation, verification\npackages/fairness/      — Fairness verification functions\npackages/config/        — Shared configuration\n```\n\n## Commands\n\n```bash\npnpm dev          # Start dev server (backend service)\npnpm dev:waitlist # Start waitlist-only entrypoint\npnpm test         # Run all tests (vitest)\npnpm lint         # Lint backend + workspace packages\npnpm lint:fix     # Lint + autofix backend + workspace packages\npnpm typecheck    # Typecheck backend + workspace packages\npnpm migrate      # Run DB migrations\npnpm format       # Format with prettier\n```\n\n## App Platform Env Contract\n\n- If you add, remove, rename, or make any runtime/deploy env var mandatory, update the repo-owned App Platform contract in the same task.\n- Update both `.do/app-dev.yaml` and `.do/app-prod.yaml`.\n- If deploy-time inputs changed, also update `.github/workflows/deploy-dev.yml`, `.github/workflows/deploy-prod.yml`, and `.do/README.md`.\n- Do not assume missing GitHub Environment vars/secrets are safe; empty values can reach App Platform as empty strings and must be handled deliberately.\n\n## Pre-commit Hook\n\n`.githooks/pre-commit` typechecks affected backend files or workspace packages when they are staged.\n\nGit must be configured to use it: `git config core.hooksPath .githooks`\n\n## Database\n\n- **Engine**: PostgreSQL 16 (via `postgres` package, typed raw SQL)\n- **Migrations**: `migrations/001_init.sql` — single consolidated file, auto-run on startup\n- **Key tables**:\n  - `rounds` — flipyou + pot shot matches (commit-reveal, CHECK on game/phase)\n  - `closecall_rounds` — Close Call pari-mutuel rounds (oracle-resolved, CHECK on phase/outcome)\n  - `game_entries` — **single source of truth** for participation + stats + leaderboard. Written at create/bet time, UPSERT'd at settlement. Has `user_id`, `side`, `is_winner`, `settled_at`.\n  - `transactions` — real on-chain SOL movements (deposit/payout/refund with tx_sig)\n  - `player_profiles` — player identity (user_id, username, avatar)\n  - `closecall_candles` — cached minute-boundary BTC prices (BRIN indexed)\n  - `auth_challenges` / `refresh_tokens` — JWT auth\n  - `referral_codes` / `referral_links` / `referral_earnings` / `referral_claims` — referral system\n  - `event_queue` — async event processing\n  - `operator_events` — operator audit log\n- **Schema conventions**: `BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY` (not BIGSERIAL), CHECK constraints on enum TEXT columns, `TIMESTAMPTZ` for all timestamps\n\n## Routes\n\n| Path prefix | Purpose |\n|-------------|---------|\n| `/auth/*` | Challenge-response JWT auth |\n| `/flipyou/*` | FlipYou create, settle, verify |\n| `/pot-shot/*` | Pot Shot create, current round |\n| `/rounds/*` | Shared round lookup, verification |\n| `/closecall/*` | Close Call betting, rounds, history |\n| `/profile/*` | Player profile, stats, transactions |\n| `/referral/*` | Referral codes, links, earnings, claims |\n| `/price/*` | SOL/USD price endpoint |\n\n## Public API Contract\n\n- Treat the public backend API as contract-first.\n- For any public route change, update in the same task:\n  - shared request/response contract\n  - runtime route parsing or serialization\n  - OpenAPI path or schema\n  - endpoint tests\n- Prefer shared validator-backed contracts over handwritten OpenAPI schemas.\n- Do not duplicate public game IDs, error shapes, or reusable envelopes.\n- Every new public route file should have a matching OpenAPI path module.\n- Keep `admin` and `internal` routes out of the public OpenAPI spec unless explicitly requested.\n- Public JSON routes must use the shared envelope body:\n  - success: `{ ok: true, data }`\n  - error: `{ ok: false, error }`\n- Preserve semantic HTTP status codes. Do not flatten handled failures into `200`.\n  - `200` / `201` / `202`: success\n  - `204`: explicit no-body success\n  - `400` / `422`: malformed or invalid request\n  - `401` / `403`: auth or permission failure\n  - `404`: missing resource\n  - `409`: conflict or invalid current state\n  - `429`: rate limit or cooldown\n- Only use `200` with nullable, empty, or default-valued payloads when the absence is the documented success answer for that route.\n- When changing a public route contract, audit status-sensitive consumers in `waitlist/`, `webapp/`, and `telegram/`, or log the rollout gap in `docs/TECH_DEBT.md`.\n- Canonical reference for this pattern: `docs/specs/304-response-envelope/spec.md`.\n\n## Settlement\n\n- **PDA watcher** (`worker/pda-watcher.ts`): WebSocket `onAccountChange` for instant join/settle detection\n- **Polling fallback** (`worker/settlement.ts`): 1s interval for resilience\n- **Close Call clock** (`worker/closecall-clock.ts`): Creates rounds on minute boundaries, settles via Pyth price\n- **Retry worker** (`worker/retry.ts`): Retries failed settlements with exponential backoff\n\n## Package Conventions\n\n- Package names: `@rng-utopia/*` (private, no npm publish)\n- All amounts in **lamports** (u64) — convert SOL only at display boundaries\n- Fees read from on-chain `PlatformConfig.fee_bps` at settlement time\n- Auth: JWT Bearer tokens via challenge-response (not per-request Ed25519 signatures)\n","numLines":110,"startLine":1,"totalLines":110}}}
