{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01D9s5rQac9pHRziFT7iNnJp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_019TVD7Bz9v1At9RXu4TS6mR","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/CLAUDE.md","old_string":"- Prefer shared validator-backed contracts over handwritten OpenAPI schemas.\n- Do not duplicate public game IDs, error shapes, or reusable envelopes.\n- Every new public route file should have a matching OpenAPI path module.\n- Keep `admin` and `internal` routes out of the public OpenAPI spec unless explicitly requested.\n- Public JSON routes must use the shared envelope body:\n  - success: `{ ok: true, data }`\n  - error: `{ ok: false, error }`\n- Preserve semantic HTTP status codes. Do not flatten handled failures into `200`.\n  - `200` / `201` / `202`: success\n  - `204`: explicit no-body success\n  - `400` / `422`: malformed or invalid request\n  - `401` / `403`: auth or permission failure\n  - `404`: missing resource\n  - `409`: conflict or invalid current state\n  - `429`: rate limit or cooldown\n- Only use `200` with nullable, empty, or default-valued payloads when the absence is the documented success answer for that route.\n- When changing a public route contract, audit status-sensitive consumers in `waitlist/`, `webapp/`, and `telegram/`, or log the rollout gap in `docs/TECH_DEBT.md`.\n- Canonical reference for this pattern: `docs/specs/304-response-envelope/spec.md`.","new_string":"- Prefer shared validator-backed contracts over handwritten OpenAPI schemas.\n- Do not duplicate public game IDs, error shapes, or reusable envelopes.\n- Every new public route file should have a matching OpenAPI path module.\n- Keep `admin` and `internal` routes out of the public OpenAPI spec unless explicitly requested.\n- When changing a public route contract, audit status-sensitive consumers in `waitlist/`, `webapp/`, and `telegram/`, or log the rollout gap in `docs/TECH_DEBT.md`.\n\n## Envelope Contract\n\nEvery public JSON response uses one of two body shapes, and HTTP status codes keep their transport/application meaning. Canonical reference: `docs/specs/304-response-envelope/spec.md`.\n\n### Body shape\n\n```ts\ntype ApiEnvelope<T> =\n  | { ok: true; data: T }                         // success\n  | { ok: false; error: ApiError };               // failure\n\ninterface ApiError {\n  code: ApiErrorCode;    // SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE, stable across versions\n  message: string;       // human-readable, may change\n  retryable?: boolean;   // whether retrying the same request may succeed\n  details?: unknown;     // optional structured metadata (zod issues, limits, etc.)\n}\n```\n\n- `ok` is the discriminator. Do not return naked `{ error: \"...\" }` or `{ success: true, ... }` bodies.\n- Error codes are drawn from the central catalog in `backend/src/contracts/api-errors.ts` (`API_ERROR_CODES`). Adding a new code is cheap; renaming a shipped code is a breaking change.\n- Exceptions that intentionally carry no body: `204 No Content` (e.g. `POST /auth/logout`) and framework-generated unmatched-route `404`/`405`.\n\n### Status semantics\n\n| Status | Meaning | Body |\n|--------|---------|------|\n| `200` | Synchronous success, including documented empty-state reads | `{ ok: true, data }` |\n| `201` | Resource created | `{ ok: true, data }` |\n| `202` | Accepted async work (e.g. `POST /referral/claim`) | `{ ok: true, data }` |\n| `204` | Success with no response body | — |\n| `400` | Malformed request / invalid identifier format | `{ ok: false, error }` |\n| `401` | Missing / invalid / expired auth | `{ ok: false, error }` |\n| `403` | Authenticated but forbidden (e.g. wallet mismatch) | `{ ok: false, error }` |\n| `404` | Resource not found when absence is exceptional | `{ ok: false, error }` |\n| `409` | Conflict / invalid current state | `{ ok: false, error }` |\n| `422` | Request validation failed (Zod / domain bounds) | `{ ok: false, error }` |\n| `429` | Rate limit / cooldown | `{ ok: false, error }` |\n| `5xx` | Server fault | `{ ok: false, error }` for handled cases |\n\n- Do not flatten handled domain failures into `200`. Validation → `422`, auth → `401/403`, cooldown → `429`, conflict → `409`, missing → `404`.\n- Only use `200` with nullable / empty / default payloads when the absence is itself the documented success answer (e.g. `GET /referral/code` → `{ code: string | null }`, `GET /referral/referrer` → all-nullable fields, `GET /points/mine` → zeroed row).\n\n### Helpers\n\nAlways emit envelopes through the shared helpers in `backend/src/contracts/api-envelope.ts`:\n\n```ts\nimport { ok, err } from \"@/contracts/api-envelope\";\nimport { API_ERROR_CODES } from \"@/contracts/api-errors\";\n\n// success\nreturn ok(c, { code: row?.code ?? null });                         // 200 default\nreturn ok(c, { claimId, status: \"pending\" }, 202);                 // explicit status\n\n// error\nreturn err(c, 404, API_ERROR_CODES.CODE_NOT_FOUND, \"Code not found\");\nreturn err(c, 422, API_ERROR_CODES.VALIDATION_FAILED, \"Invalid request\", {\n  retryable: false,\n  details: zodError.issues,\n});\n```\n\n### OpenAPI\n\n- Every declared `application/json` response at a 2xx status must be `envelope(SuccessSchema)`.\n- Every declared `application/json` response at a 4xx/5xx status must be `ErrorEnvelopeSchema` (or an equivalent inline `{ ok: false, error }` shape).\n- `ApiError` and `ErrorEnvelope` are registered once as OpenAPI components — reference them via `$ref`, do not re-inline.\n- The contract tests `backend/src/__tests__/openapi-contract.test.ts` and `waitlist-contract.test.ts` enforce both rules at build time."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2583,"cache_read_input_tokens":72012,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2583,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":47,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"736bbedb-6401-4318-a325-ee85001d8ebf","uuid":"ea48c446-164e-44e0-a5af-18ed3f38b9c9"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019TVD7Bz9v1At9RXu4TS6mR","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/CLAUDE.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"736bbedb-6401-4318-a325-ee85001d8ebf","uuid":"ba9c011d-1e1d-4d88-b4e0-5b36f4b1eaac","timestamp":"2026-04-22T11:21:29.136Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/backend/CLAUDE.md","oldString":"- Prefer shared validator-backed contracts over handwritten OpenAPI schemas.\n- Do not duplicate public game IDs, error shapes, or reusable envelopes.\n- Every new public route file should have a matching OpenAPI path module.\n- Keep `admin` and `internal` routes out of the public OpenAPI spec unless explicitly requested.\n- Public JSON routes must use the shared envelope body:\n  - success: `{ ok: true, data }`\n  - error: `{ ok: false, error }`\n- Preserve semantic HTTP status codes. Do not flatten handled failures into `200`.\n  - `200` / `201` / `202`: success\n  - `204`: explicit no-body success\n  - `400` / `422`: malformed or invalid request\n  - `401` / `403`: auth or permission failure\n  - `404`: missing resource\n  - `409`: conflict or invalid current state\n  - `429`: rate limit or cooldown\n- Only use `200` with nullable, empty, or default-valued payloads when the absence is the documented success answer for that route.\n- When changing a public route contract, audit status-sensitive consumers in `waitlist/`, `webapp/`, and `telegram/`, or log the rollout gap in `docs/TECH_DEBT.md`.\n- Canonical reference for this pattern: `docs/specs/304-response-envelope/spec.md`.","newString":"- Prefer shared validator-backed contracts over handwritten OpenAPI schemas.\n- Do not duplicate public game IDs, error shapes, or reusable envelopes.\n- Every new public route file should have a matching OpenAPI path module.\n- Keep `admin` and `internal` routes out of the public OpenAPI spec unless explicitly requested.\n- When changing a public route contract, audit status-sensitive consumers in `waitlist/`, `webapp/`, and `telegram/`, or log the rollout gap in `docs/TECH_DEBT.md`.\n\n## Envelope Contract\n\nEvery public JSON response uses one of two body shapes, and HTTP status codes keep their transport/application meaning. Canonical reference: `docs/specs/304-response-envelope/spec.md`.\n\n### Body shape\n\n```ts\ntype ApiEnvelope<T> =\n  | { ok: true; data: T }                         // success\n  | { ok: false; error: ApiError };               // failure\n\ninterface ApiError {\n  code: ApiErrorCode;    // SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE, stable across versions\n  message: string;       // human-readable, may change\n  retryable?: boolean;   // whether retrying the same request may succeed\n  details?: unknown;     // optional structured metadata (zod issues, limits, etc.)\n}\n```\n\n- `ok` is the discriminator. Do not return naked `{ error: \"...\" }` or `{ success: true, ... }` bodies.\n- Error codes are drawn from the central catalog in `backend/src/contracts/api-errors.ts` (`API_ERROR_CODES`). Adding a new code is cheap; renaming a shipped code is a breaking change.\n- Exceptions that intentionally carry no body: `204 No Content` (e.g. `POST /auth/logout`) and framework-generated unmatched-route `404`/`405`.\n\n### Status semantics\n\n| Status | Meaning | Body |\n|--------|---------|------|\n| `200` | Synchronous success, including documented empty-state reads | `{ ok: true, data }` |\n| `201` | Resource created | `{ ok: true, data }` |\n| `202` | Accepted async work (e.g. `POST /referral/claim`) | `{ ok: true, data }` |\n| `204` | Success with no response body | — |\n| `400` | Malformed request / invalid identifier format | `{ ok: false, error }` |\n| `401` | Missing / invalid / expired auth | `{ ok: false, error }` |\n| `403` | Authenticated but forbidden (e.g. wallet mismatch) | `{ ok: false, error }` |\n| `404` | Resource not found when absence is exceptional | `{ ok: false, error }` |\n| `409` | Conflict / invalid current state | `{ ok: false, error }` |\n| `422` | Request validation failed (Zod / domain bounds) | `{ ok: false, error }` |\n| `429` | Rate limit / cooldown | `{ ok: false, error }` |\n| `5xx` | Server fault | `{ ok: false, error }` for handled cases |\n\n- Do not flatten handled domain failures into `200`. Validation → `422`, auth → `401/403`, cooldown → `429`, conflict → `409`, missing → `404`.\n- Only use `200` with nullable / empty / default payloads when the absence is itself the documented success answer (e.g. `GET /referral/code` → `{ code: string | null }`, `GET /referral/referrer` → all-nullable fields, `GET /points/mine` → zeroed row).\n\n### Helpers\n\nAlways emit envelopes through the shared helpers in `backend/src/contracts/api-envelope.ts`:\n\n```ts\nimport { ok, err } from \"@/contracts/api-envelope\";\nimport { API_ERROR_CODES } from \"@/contracts/api-errors\";\n\n// success\nreturn ok(c, { code: row?.code ?? null });                         // 200 default\nreturn ok(c, { claimId, status: \"pending\" }, 202);                 // explicit status\n\n// error\nreturn err(c, 404, API_ERROR_CODES.CODE_NOT_FOUND, \"Code not found\");\nreturn err(c, 422, API_ERROR_CODES.VALIDATION_FAILED, \"Invalid request\", {\n  retryable: false,\n  details: zodError.issues,\n});\n```\n\n### OpenAPI\n\n- Every declared `application/json` response at a 2xx status must be `envelope(SuccessSchema)`.\n- Every declared `application/json` response at a 4xx/5xx status must be `ErrorEnvelopeSchema` (or an equivalent inline `{ ok: false, error }` shape).\n- `ApiError` and `ErrorEnvelope` are registered once as OpenAPI components — reference them via `$ref`, do not re-inline.\n- The contract tests `backend/src/__tests__/openapi-contract.test.ts` and `waitlist-contract.test.ts` enforce both rules at build time.","originalFile":"# Backend — Developer Guide\n\n## Structure\n\n```text\nsrc/                    — Hono API server, routes, workers, middleware, waitlist entrypoint\nmigrations/             — SQL migrations auto-run on startup\npackages/anchor-client/ — IDL bridge (generated from solana/target/)\npackages/game-engine/   — Game logic, PDA derivation, verification\npackages/fairness/      — Fairness verification functions\npackages/config/        — Shared configuration\n```\n\n## Commands\n\n```bash\npnpm dev          # Start dev server (backend service)\npnpm dev:waitlist # Start waitlist-only entrypoint\npnpm test         # Run all tests (vitest)\npnpm lint         # Lint backend + workspace packages\npnpm lint:fix     # Lint + autofix backend + workspace packages\npnpm typecheck    # Typecheck backend + workspace packages\npnpm migrate      # Run DB migrations\npnpm format       # Format with prettier\n```\n\n## App Platform Env Contract\n\n- If you add, remove, rename, or make any runtime/deploy env var mandatory, update the repo-owned App Platform contract in the same task.\n- Update both `.do/app-dev.yaml` and `.do/app-prod.yaml`.\n- If deploy-time inputs changed, also update `.github/workflows/deploy-dev.yml`, `.github/workflows/deploy-prod.yml`, and `.do/README.md`.\n- Do not assume missing GitHub Environment vars/secrets are safe; empty values can reach App Platform as empty strings and must be handled deliberately.\n\n## Pre-commit Hook\n\n`.githooks/pre-commit` typechecks affected backend files or workspace packages when they are staged.\n\nGit must be configured to use it: `git config core.hooksPath .githooks`\n\n## Database\n\n- **Engine**: PostgreSQL 16 (via `postgres` package, typed raw SQL)\n- **Migrations**: `migrations/001_init.sql` — single consolidated file, auto-run on startup\n- **Key tables**:\n  - `rounds` — flipyou + pot shot matches (commit-reveal, CHECK on game/phase)\n  - `closecall_rounds` — Close Call pari-mutuel rounds (oracle-resolved, CHECK on phase/outcome)\n  - `game_entries` — **single source of truth** for participation + stats + leaderboard. Written at create/bet time, UPSERT'd at settlement. Has `user_id`, `side`, `is_winner`, `settled_at`.\n  - `transactions` — real on-chain SOL movements (deposit/payout/refund with tx_sig)\n  - `player_profiles` — player identity (user_id, username, avatar)\n  - `closecall_candles` — cached minute-boundary BTC prices (BRIN indexed)\n  - `auth_challenges` / `refresh_tokens` — JWT auth\n  - `referral_codes` / `referral_links` / `referral_earnings` / `referral_claims` — referral system\n  - `event_queue` — async event processing\n  - `operator_events` — operator audit log\n- **Schema conventions**: `BIGINT GENERATED ALWAYS AS IDENTITY` (not BIGSERIAL), CHECK constraints on enum TEXT columns, `TIMESTAMPTZ` for all timestamps\n\n## Routes\n\n| Path prefix | Purpose |\n|-------------|---------|\n| `/auth/*` | Challenge-response JWT auth |\n| `/flipyou/*` | FlipYou create, settle, verify |\n| `/pot-shot/*` | Pot Shot create, current round |\n| `/rounds/*` | Shared round lookup, verification |\n| `/closecall/*` | Close Call betting, rounds, history |\n| `/profile/*` | Player profile, stats, transactions |\n| `/referral/*` | Referral codes, links, earnings, claims |\n| `/price/*` | SOL/USD price endpoint |\n\n## Public API Contract\n\n- Treat the public backend API as contract-first.\n- For any public route change, update in the same task:\n  - shared request/response contract\n  - runtime route parsing or serialization\n  - OpenAPI path or schema\n  - endpoint tests\n- Prefer shared validator-backed contracts over handwritten OpenAPI schemas.\n- Do not duplicate public game IDs, error shapes, or reusable envelopes.\n- Every new public route file should have a matching OpenAPI path module.\n- Keep `admin` and `internal` routes out of the public OpenAPI spec unless explicitly requested.\n- Public JSON routes must use the shared envelope body:\n  - success: `{ ok: true, data }`\n  - error: `{ ok: false, error }`\n- Preserve semantic HTTP status codes. Do not flatten handled failures into `200`.\n  - `200` / `201` / `202`: success\n  - `204`: explicit no-body success\n  - `400` / `422`: malformed or invalid request\n  - `401` / `403`: auth or permission failure\n  - `404`: missing resource\n  - `409`: conflict or invalid current state\n  - `429`: rate limit or cooldown\n- Only use `200` with nullable, empty, or default-valued payloads when the absence is the documented success answer for that route.\n- When changing a public route contract, audit status-sensitive consumers in `waitlist/`, `webapp/`, and `telegram/`, or log the rollout gap in `docs/TECH_DEBT.md`.\n- Canonical reference for this pattern: `docs/specs/304-response-envelope/spec.md`.\n\n## Settlement\n\n- **PDA watcher** (`worker/pda-watcher.ts`): WebSocket `onAccountChange` for instant join/settle detection\n- **Polling fallback** (`worker/settlement.ts`): 1s interval for resilience\n- **Close Call clock** (`worker/closecall-clock.ts`): Creates rounds on minute boundaries, settles via Pyth price\n- **Retry worker** (`worker/retry.ts`): Retries failed settlements with exponential backoff\n\n## Package Conventions\n\n- Package names: `@rng-utopia/*` (private, no npm publish)\n- All amounts in **lamports** (u64) — convert SOL only at display boundaries\n- Fees read from on-chain `PlatformConfig.fee_bps` at settlement time\n- Auth: JWT Bearer tokens via challenge-response (not per-request Ed25519 signatures)\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":79,"oldLines":21,"newStart":79,"newLines":78,"lines":[" - Do not duplicate public game IDs, error shapes, or reusable envelopes."," - Every new public route file should have a matching OpenAPI path module."," - Keep `admin` and `internal` routes out of the public OpenAPI spec unless explicitly requested.","-- Public JSON routes must use the shared envelope body:","-  - success: `{ ok: true, data }`","-  - error: `{ ok: false, error }`","-- Preserve semantic HTTP status codes. Do not flatten handled failures into `200`.","-  - `200` / `201` / `202`: success","-  - `204`: explicit no-body success","-  - `400` / `422`: malformed or invalid request","-  - `401` / `403`: auth or permission failure","-  - `404`: missing resource","-  - `409`: conflict or invalid current state","-  - `429`: rate limit or cooldown","-- Only use `200` with nullable, empty, or default-valued payloads when the absence is the documented success answer for that route."," - When changing a public route contract, audit status-sensitive consumers in `waitlist/`, `webapp/`, and `telegram/`, or log the rollout gap in `docs/TECH_DEBT.md`.","-- Canonical reference for this pattern: `docs/specs/304-response-envelope/spec.md`."," ","+## Envelope Contract","+","+Every public JSON response uses one of two body shapes, and HTTP status codes keep their transport/application meaning. Canonical reference: `docs/specs/304-response-envelope/spec.md`.","+","+### Body shape","+","+```ts","+type ApiEnvelope<T> =","+  | { ok: true; data: T }                         // success","+  | { ok: false; error: ApiError };               // failure","+","+interface ApiError {","+  code: ApiErrorCode;    // SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE, stable across versions","+  message: string;       // human-readable, may change","+  retryable?: boolean;   // whether retrying the same request may succeed","+  details?: unknown;     // optional structured metadata (zod issues, limits, etc.)","+}","+```","+","+- `ok` is the discriminator. Do not return naked `{ error: \"...\" }` or `{ success: true, ... }` bodies.","+- Error codes are drawn from the central catalog in `backend/src/contracts/api-errors.ts` (`API_ERROR_CODES`). Adding a new code is cheap; renaming a shipped code is a breaking change.","+- Exceptions that intentionally carry no body: `204 No Content` (e.g. `POST /auth/logout`) and framework-generated unmatched-route `404`/`405`.","+","+### Status semantics","+","+| Status | Meaning | Body |","+|--------|---------|------|","+| `200` | Synchronous success, including documented empty-state reads | `{ ok: true, data }` |","+| `201` | Resource created | `{ ok: true, data }` |","+| `202` | Accepted async work (e.g. `POST /referral/claim`) | `{ ok: true, data }` |","+| `204` | Success with no response body | — |","+| `400` | Malformed request / invalid identifier format | `{ ok: false, error }` |","+| `401` | Missing / invalid / expired auth | `{ ok: false, error }` |","+| `403` | Authenticated but forbidden (e.g. wallet mismatch) | `{ ok: false, error }` |","+| `404` | Resource not found when absence is exceptional | `{ ok: false, error }` |","+| `409` | Conflict / invalid current state | `{ ok: false, error }` |","+| `422` | Request validation failed (Zod / domain bounds) | `{ ok: false, error }` |","+| `429` | Rate limit / cooldown | `{ ok: false, error }` |","+| `5xx` | Server fault | `{ ok: false, error }` for handled cases |","+","+- Do not flatten handled domain failures into `200`. Validation → `422`, auth → `401/403`, cooldown → `429`, conflict → `409`, missing → `404`.","+- Only use `200` with nullable / empty / default payloads when the absence is itself the documented success answer (e.g. `GET /referral/code` → `{ code: string | null }`, `GET /referral/referrer` → all-nullable fields, `GET /points/mine` → zeroed row).","+","+### Helpers","+","+Always emit envelopes through the shared helpers in `backend/src/contracts/api-envelope.ts`:","+","+```ts","+import { ok, err } from \"@/contracts/api-envelope\";","+import { API_ERROR_CODES } from \"@/contracts/api-errors\";","+","+// success","+return ok(c, { code: row?.code ?? null });                         // 200 default","+return ok(c, { claimId, status: \"pending\" }, 202);                 // explicit status","+","+// error","+return err(c, 404, API_ERROR_CODES.CODE_NOT_FOUND, \"Code not found\");","+return err(c, 422, API_ERROR_CODES.VALIDATION_FAILED, \"Invalid request\", {","+  retryable: false,","+  details: zodError.issues,","+});","+```","+","+### OpenAPI","+","+- Every declared `application/json` response at a 2xx status must be `envelope(SuccessSchema)`.","+- Every declared `application/json` response at a 4xx/5xx status must be `ErrorEnvelopeSchema` (or an equivalent inline `{ ok: false, error }` shape).","+- `ApiError` and `ErrorEnvelope` are registered once as OpenAPI components — reference them via `$ref`, do not re-inline.","+- The contract tests `backend/src/__tests__/openapi-contract.test.ts` and `waitlist-contract.test.ts` enforce both rules at build time.","+"," ## Settlement"," "," - **PDA watcher** (`worker/pda-watcher.ts`): WebSocket `onAccountChange` for instant join/settle detection"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
